title: Prepared a basic test script
message:
Prepared a basic test script

It will give you a file called "Result.csv".
Here is the complete procedure:
- Make sure you have OpenCV installed and its libraries are findable by linker (somethig like "export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=../opencv/lib" might be useful)
- Clone this git repository: https://github.com/pakdel/AndroidBacteriaImageProcessing.git
- Download "IDEOS" and "Nexus" directories ( complete, with their .jpg files)
- Download "Lab Test Results" SpreadSheet as a .csv file ("Lab Test Results - Sheet1.csv")
- Run the test.pl script and pass the .csv file to it: ./test.pl "Lab Test Results - Sheet1.csv"
- Results will be in "Result.csv" file

title: renaming activities and variables to reflect new conventions:
message:
renaming activities and variables to reflect new conventions:

Source -> is a well or tap or puddle or other source
Sample -> is a bottle or jug or bag of water that will be used to make tests
Test -> is one of 5 tests that can be done on the water, one of which is the petrifilm test which we are focusing on since it is the most tedious and complex for humans

Fixes #28

To summarize, to use NDK:
*Need path to OpenCV defined as an evironment variable
*Need a builder defined
*Need Android.mk which does includes and declares source files
*In the source files .cpp need the package name and java class where the function will be called
